Students leaving the Durban Magistrate's Court following Thabani Mzolo's appearance on Thursday morning. 
Video: Karen Singh

MUT SRC President, Sandile Dlamini, said there was enough evidence for the court to Mzolo to jail and not grant him bail. 
He said he has asked MUT to arrange for counselling for the female student who witnessed the shooting. 
"They need to arrange psychological counselling for her because she needs to be in a good frame of mind when she returns to campus," he said. 
Dlamini said he has been in contact with Khumalo's family who are battling to come to terms with the murder. 
He rubbished claims that MUT had an outsourced security company guarding the res. 
"That is nonsense. If a university sends a person to a building, that person is registered with the university and not with the building," Dlamini said. 
The Mercury